Key Match Events: Donyell Malen scored an own goal in the 6th minute
Cody Gakpo equalised for the Netherlands in the second half
Romano Schmid put Austria ahead again in the 59th minute
Memphis Depay equalised for the Netherlands in the 75th minute
Marcel Sabitzer scored a late winner for Austria in the 80th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Marcel Sabitzer praised his team's performance and said winning the group was the most important thing
Dutch captain Virgil van Dijk described the match as 'a bad evening' and said the team started weakly in possession and in duels
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria topped the table with six points, one ahead of second-placed France on five and the Dutch on four points
The match was played at the Olympiastadion in Berlin, Germany, in front of an attendance of 68,363
Others: The result of the match meant that Austria will next meet the Group F runners-up, while France and the Netherlands wait to find out the identity of their last-16 opponents
